I guess not.

770
00:40:39,304 --> 00:40:40,572
He's obnoxious...

771
00:40:43,408 --> 00:40:45,277
he's a blockhead...

772
00:40:47,345 --> 00:40:49,581
He's wishy-washy...

773
00:40:51,783 --> 00:40:54,686
He has no self-confidence...

774
00:40:55,453 --> 00:40:57,722
But that's who Masakazu is.

775
00:40:58,990 --> 00:41:00,792
It'd be no fun if he changed.

776
00:41:03,728 --> 00:41:06,364
If I wanted him to change, it
could've been anybody else.

777
00:41:07,265 --> 00:41:08,266
It can be Yamaji.

778
00:41:08,400 --> 00:41:10,001
Yeah... huh?

779
00:41:16,374 --> 00:41:18,109
I'm quitting my job.

780
00:41:21,012 --> 00:41:22,948
I'm not going to Sendai.

781
00:41:26,084 --> 00:41:29,221
I want to be with the
no-good Masakazu.

782
00:41:33,792 --> 00:41:37,329
But I can't tell him that.

783
00:41:44,069 --> 00:41:47,072
I'm a boring woman.

784
00:41:49,441 --> 00:41:51,209
That's not true.

785
00:41:54,579 --> 00:41:56,448
You're a fine woman,
Akane-chan.

786
00:41:57,515 --> 00:41:58,750
You'd be wasted on me.

787
00:41:59,684 --> 00:42:00,752
Hand me the towel.

788
00:42:05,690 --> 00:42:07,158
So...

789
00:42:07,292 --> 00:42:08,159
Are you doing it?

790
00:42:09,961 --> 00:42:11,429
Or not?

791
00:42:11,563 --> 00:42:14,199
Stop kidding around.
We're having a serious talk.

792
00:42:15,934 --> 00:42:17,202
Gosh...

793
00:42:18,370 --> 00:42:19,938
I told Masakazu-kun...

794
00:42:21,640 --> 00:42:23,875
that although I can be your
conversational companion...

795
00:42:25,944 --> 00:42:28,313
I'm incapable of making
you happy.

796
00:42:32,250 --> 00:42:33,685
The only person who
can make you happy...

797
00:42:36,888 --> 00:42:38,523
And that was all.

798
00:42:39,024 --> 00:42:40,325
I dunno...

799
00:42:40,458 --> 00:42:42,060
maybe it's because
Yamaji told the story...

800
00:42:42,193 --> 00:42:43,995
I felt like crying and yet
I couldn't.

801
00:42:44,095 --> 00:42:45,196
What's that supposed to mean?

802
00:42:47,532 --> 00:42:48,733
He's crying.

803
00:42:49,367 --> 00:42:50,669
You see...

804
00:42:51,369 --> 00:42:52,203
I should've gone...

805
00:42:52,304 --> 00:42:54,272
on that trip with her.

806
00:42:54,406 --> 00:42:55,974
I thought that too.

807
00:42:56,107 --> 00:42:58,443
But if you guys went, you'd
sleep together and it'd be all over.

808
00:42:58,977 --> 00:43:00,378
I'll zip it.

809
00:43:03,982 --> 00:43:04,950
So...

810
00:43:05,784 --> 00:43:06,851
are you going to ask her back?

811
00:43:08,787 --> 00:43:09,621
No...

812
00:43:11,690 --> 00:43:13,124
after hearing what you'd said...

813
00:43:14,326 --> 00:43:15,493
I definitely can't ask her.

814
00:43:15,627 --> 00:43:17,862
- Why?
- Because I want to change.

815
00:43:18,697 --> 00:43:19,564
If...

816
00:43:21,533 --> 00:43:23,335
I can't change...

817
00:43:25,837 --> 00:43:27,138
it'd be unbearable.

818
00:43:30,809 --> 00:43:33,211
I'm so glad, Yutori
got hired.

819
00:43:33,311 --> 00:43:34,813
Ta-da.

820
00:43:35,947 --> 00:43:37,816
Oh.

821
00:43:37,949 --> 00:43:39,250
"Oh"? Is that all?

822
00:43:39,351 --> 00:43:41,586
That's right, we must celebrate.

823
00:43:41,686 --> 00:43:44,322
Your boyfriend will celebrate it
for you, won't he?

824
00:43:46,524 --> 00:43:48,693
I got an order from
Masakazu's shop...

825
00:43:49,127 --> 00:43:51,429
for "Demon Bride's
Tears" and

826
00:43:51,563 --> 00:43:55,233
"Little Sister-in-Law", officially.

827
00:43:55,367 --> 00:43:57,535
Oh. I see.

828
00:43:57,669 --> 00:43:59,237
Sorry about the terrible names.

829
00:44:00,038 --> 00:44:01,539
Here's the extra order of
"Little Sister-in-Law".

830
00:44:01,639 --> 00:44:02,974
Thank you very much.

831
00:44:03,108 --> 00:44:05,076
I think he's finally
getting serious.

832
00:44:05,710 --> 00:44:06,911
I'll go lend a hand.

833
00:44:07,946 --> 00:44:09,280
Come on, let's go eat.

834
00:44:13,752 --> 00:44:14,953
You got hired?

835
00:44:15,086 --> 00:44:16,154
Congratulations.

836
00:44:16,721 --> 00:44:18,156
We should celebrate.

837
00:44:18,790 --> 00:44:20,725
Yeah... that's true.

838
00:44:21,192 --> 00:44:21,993
Yeah.

839
00:44:22,293 --> 00:44:23,995
I'll fade out slowly.

840
00:44:24,529 --> 00:44:26,197
Huh? Yeah.

841
00:44:26,331 --> 00:44:28,500
Yeah. Yeah. Yeah.

842
00:44:28,600 --> 00:44:29,901
Right away, yes.

843
00:44:30,001 --> 00:44:31,036
We'll break up right away.

844
00:44:31,169 --> 00:44:33,038
Sorry, I'm at work now.
Let's talk later.

845
00:44:36,141 --> 00:44:38,209
- Was it crowded?
- Not at all.

846
00:44:38,309 --> 00:44:40,578
- It's a weekday.
- True.

847
00:44:41,012 --> 00:44:42,580
It's kind of noisy here.

848
00:44:42,847 --> 00:44:44,783
There's been a little problem.

849
00:44:46,951 --> 00:44:48,620
- Sorry to interrupt...
- What?

850
00:44:50,155 --> 00:44:51,990
Miyashita-san. Thank you,
regarding the rice wine.

851
00:44:52,123 --> 00:44:55,493
Oh, sure. They decided the wines
give personality to the shops.

852
00:44:56,194 --> 00:44:57,829
Where are you crutches?

853
00:44:58,363 --> 00:44:59,764
Oh no. I forgot them.

854
00:45:00,398 --> 00:45:01,332
Anyway...

855
00:45:02,000 --> 00:45:03,701
go to Nogami-san's,
right away.

856
00:45:04,102 --> 00:45:05,437
- Huh?
- He has food poisoning.

857
00:45:05,570 --> 00:45:06,371
Huh?

858
00:45:06,471 --> 00:45:10,942
Out of all the customers who
ate the shipped bento...

859
00:45:11,042 --> 00:45:13,311
30 people were taken sick
to a nearby hospital.

860
00:45:13,645 --> 00:45:15,980
According to investigation...

861
00:45:16,114 --> 00:45:17,649
Isn't that Masakazu's...

862
00:45:17,782 --> 00:45:19,017
client?

863
00:45:19,150 --> 00:45:20,251
What?

864
00:45:22,020 --> 00:45:23,054
They were expired?

865
00:45:23,188 --> 00:45:25,690
They repackaged expired
bentos and sold them.

866
00:45:26,157 --> 00:45:27,725
Sounds like something
Nogami-san would do.

867
00:45:27,859 --> 00:45:28,993
Where's Yamagishi?

868
00:45:29,127 --> 00:45:30,395
I cannot reach him.

869
00:45:30,728 --> 00:45:31,930
That guy again...

870
00:45:32,063 --> 00:45:33,832
Division chief Hayakawa is
there already.

871
00:45:33,932 --> 00:45:34,933
You go there now too.

872
00:45:35,567 --> 00:45:37,769
- Yes.
- But before you go...

873
00:45:37,902 --> 00:45:39,170
I know the timing is odd, but...

874
00:45:40,105 --> 00:45:41,406
This man here...

875
00:45:44,542 --> 00:45:45,477
Yes.

876
00:45:45,877 --> 00:45:47,812
- He's my father.
- What?

877
00:45:48,413 --> 00:45:49,247
That's him?

878
00:45:50,582 --> 00:45:51,783
Well now...

879
00:45:52,484 --> 00:45:53,918
I am Miyashita Akane's father.

880
00:45:53,985 --> 00:45:56,020
I have arrived from Saga,
just today.

881
00:45:58,189 --> 00:46:01,059
- We are sorry.
- This is food poisoning.

882
00:46:01,192 --> 00:46:02,861
Office workers are in a battle.

883
00:46:02,961 --> 00:46:04,929
You have to be more ashamed.

884
00:46:05,063 --> 00:46:05,897
You and me both.

885
00:46:05,997 --> 00:46:07,932
Yamaji's here.

886
00:46:08,199 --> 00:46:09,000
A gardener?

887
00:46:09,100 --> 00:46:10,935
I do love Akane-san.

888
00:46:11,069 --> 00:46:12,837
But I do not like her father.

